Abide	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Brother, he was described as mystic and advised caution during a meeting of Pures at the Altar of Judgment upon the Great Spire of Kolanse.<br>
Absi	The son of Onos T'oolan and Hetan, of mixed Barghast and Imass heritage. His Imass name is Kire, meaning Autumn Promise, and he is a happy child with strangely large, wide hands and stubby fingers. He is untroubled by presences that might frighten others, including ancient soldiers and wolves, giving him a calm, unusual composure.<br>
Aimanan	A Jaghut warrior of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
Aloft	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Brother, he commanded fifteen thousand Shriven auxiliaries supporting the forces of Sister Freedom and Brother Grave, and rode a bone-white Jhag horse.<br>
Aparal Forge	A Tiste Liosan Soletaken Eleint associated with Kessobahn's blood and Kadagar Fant's circle.<br>
Belie	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Sister.<br>
Beroke Soft Voice	A name used by the Teblor for Ber'ok, one of the broken T'lan Imass known as the Unbound and one of the Seven Faces in the Rock. His Imass name means Dead Ash Tree. He has a twisted neck that leaves his head leaning to one side, and his soft voice is a rough rasp through a crushed throat.<br>
Burnt Rope	A Kartoolian sapper in the marine section of the Bonehunters, described as having an oiled beard.<br>
Cellows	A sergeant of the Shake. Burly and hulking, with a touch of Teblor blood in him, he carries a heavy physical presence within the Shake forces.<br>
Diligence	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Brother, he is second in seniority to Sister Reverence and her closest ally. Slope-shouldered, tall, ancient, and male, he embodies the severe hierarchy and austere authority of the Forkrul Assail leadership.<br>
Eldat Pressan	The youngest and boldest of the thirteen Tiste Liosan Soletaken Eleint. In sembled form she was bright-eyed, laughing, and beautiful, drawing the attention of younger Liosan nobles while fixing her own interest on Kadagar Fant.<br>
Equity	A Forkrul Assail Pure in Kolanse, counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Sister, she held to the Forkrul Assail dream of a world brought into balance and peace, imagining survivors forced into a new way of living under their implacable guidance.<br>
Exigent	One of the Watered.<br>
Festian	A High Watered of the Forkrul Assail armies in Kolanse.<br>
Freedom	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Sister.<br>
Gaelar Throe	A member of the elite Tiste Liosan Seventh Legion under Aparal Forge. He was tall and extremely self-assured, with a loud, harsh voice.<br>
Gallimada	A spelling used for Gillimada, a Teblor woman who leads three hundred of her people. Chosen for leadership because she is considered the most beautiful, she is short for a Teblor yet still towers over humans. Her brother Gand calls her Gilli and teases her about her height.<br>
Gathras	A Jaghut warrior of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
Gaunt-Eye	Sergeant of the 18th Squad of the Bonehunters, originally from Genabackis. His corporal Rib considers him the meanest sergeant he has ever met, while Sinter calls him tactless and harsh. He lacks a friendly face, but has one people remember for all the wrong things in it.<br>
Grave	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors. Also styled Brother, he had a thin voice and commanded Kolanse infantry alongside Sister Freedom.<br>
Haggraf	One of the High Watered.<br>
Halad the Giant	A Teblor name for Haran'alle, one of the broken T'lan Imass known as the Unbound and one of the Seven Faces in the Rock. Also called Halad Rack Bearer and Antler From Summer, he is the largest of the Unbound. He wears a headdress resembling, or stylising, a woolly elephant skull.<br>
Haut	A Jaghut warrior of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
Hestand	One of the Watered, serving as an officer under Diligence. He was ordered to ready a mounted battalion and a full supply train with provisions for at least three legions.<br>
Himble Thrup	A Bonehunters soldier, short, round-faced, and scrawny, with watery eyes. Pores thought of him as an old man.<br>
Iparth Erule	A Tiste Liosan among the thirteen who drank Kessobahn's life blood and became Soletaken Eleint. In dragon form he had golden scales and white wings.<br>
Jastara	A woman of the White Face Barghast, from clan Gilk, who becomes wife to the eldest son of Gall, Warleader of the Khundryl Burned Tears. She and her husband have children, linking Barghast and Khundryl family lines through marriage and kinship.<br>
Kadagar Fant	A Tiste Liosan known as Lord of Light, an honorific comparable to Lord of Darkness among the Tiste Andii. Son of Krin Ne Fant, a former Champion of High House Light, he controlled the Hounds of Light and counted Aparal Forge as his closest friend and advisor.<br>
Kahlb the Silent Hunter	A Teblor name for one of the seven broken T'lan Imass known as the Unbound and worshipped as the Seven Faces in the Rock. His unknown Imass name means Red Moss. The Teblor title emphasises silence and predatory watchfulness, fitting his place among the grim patron figures of Teblor tradition.<br>
Kessgan	A High Watered.<br>
Korabas	The Otataral Dragon, an enormous dragon whose aspect is otataral. Her nature links her to the magic-negating substance feared by sorcerers, making her one of the most conceptually dangerous Eleint figures in the setting.<br>
Lap Twirl	A cutter in the Malazan Bonehunters, a Falari with long blood-streaked-gold hair and the tip of his nose cut off.<br>
Nithe	A corporal in Yedan Derryg's watch. Burly and dark-bearded, he is one of the Shake soldiers serving under the Watch's command.<br>
Placid	A Forkrul Assail Pure counted among the Lawful Inquisitors.<br>
Reverence	A Forkrul Assail Pure and one of the Lawful Inquisitors. The eldest of the Assail near the Great Spire, she is tall even for her race, exceedingly gaunt, almost skeletal, with sickly grey skin bruised around the joints. Ancient and physically marked by long existence, she has a missing eye, a collapsed brow ridge, and a limp. Brother Diligence is next to her in seniority and her closest ally.<br>
Rib	A corporal in the Malazan Bonehunters, serving in the 18th Squad under Sergeant Gaunt-Eye. He considered Gaunt-Eye the meanest sergeant he had ever met.<br>
Sad	A young squad mage of the 22nd Squad in the marine section of the Bonehunters, dark-skinned, with black hair and startling blue eyes.<br>
Sanad	Also called Senad, a Jaghut warrior of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
Serenity	A Forkrul Assail: tall, spectral, white-skinned, and pallid-haired, with limp strands of hair and a leather harness wrinkled and blackened with rot. His words frame peace as something asserted against disorder, reflecting the Forkrul Assail tendency to turn abstract ideals into implacable doctrine.<br>
Sharl	A capable Shake woman who has long looked after her two younger brothers, Casel and Oruth. Her mother was a drunk, leaving her to become the responsible one in the family. She carries a pike, giving her a practical place among the Shake defenders.<br>
Spultatha	A daughter of Abrastal, Queen of Bolkando in central Lether. She is noted as having eyes just like her mother's, linking her visually and dynastically to the Bolkando royal house.<br>
Suvalas	A Jaghut warrior of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
Thenik the Shattered|Thenik	A Teblor name for Thek Ist, one of the seven broken T'lan Imass known as the Unbound and worshipped as the Seven Faces in the Rock. His Imass name means Spear Leg, while the Teblor title emphasises his shattered aspect among their ancient god-faces.<br>
Tulas Shorn	A name used by Kagamandra Tulas, a Tiste Edur Soletaken Eleint and cousin to Anomander Rake. Tall and gaunt, he is associated with mastery over beasts and with the Hounds of Shadow, giving him an ancient, predatory connection to Shadow's most feared servants.<br>
Urugal the Woven	A Teblor name for Urual, one of the broken T'lan Imass known as the Unbound and worshipped as the Seven Faces in the Rock. His Imass name means Mossy Bone, and among the Teblor he is one of the fiercest of the seven gods, the Face of the Uryd clan. Squat, heavy-boned, shorter than a regular human but much broader, he is bound with leather and hide straps and speaks in a broken rasp.<br>
Varandas	A female Jaghut and captain of the group known as the Fourteen. This group first appeared in the Wastelands of Lether around the time of the Bonehunters' arrival in the Letherii Empire.<br>
